What makes uncollateralized lending different?

If someone wants to borrow from the pool, their risk of default needs added oversight and approval.

In TrueFI, uncollateralized lenders submit a proposal and TrustToken holders vote to approve it, like a decentralized loan officer.
We send folks trying to earn yield on TrueCurrencies to @CelsiusNetwork üëå
Note that, for at least a while, TrueFi is going to lend to a smaller number of larger borrowers, rather than thousands of small ones
